title: For Sale:  Remington rolling block Mod. 4 takedown, .32rf
postcontent:
This .32 rimfire rifle has a 22.5” octagon barrel.  I have owned it for about 50 years.  It is in above average condition.  Everything including the screws appear to be original.  I am not an expert on grading firearms so you will have to judge by the attached photos.  I have never fired it but it appears fully functional.

I refinished the stock with linseed oil about 50 years ago.  (Yeah, I know.)  There is a small chip out of the top left rear of the receiver where it meets the stock. The joint of the stock and receiver is slightly loose.

The rifling depth is good but there is some corrosion in the barrel.  I have never cleaned it.

The Serial Number appears to be: JK255925.  I have been unable to find what year this would have been made.  Model 4’s were made from 1890 - 1933.  Take-down models were first introduced in 1902.  Octagon barrels were discontinued on the Model 4 in August 1924.  This narrows the date for this specific rifle to 1902-1924.

title: For Sale:  Folding Adapter for the Tapco SKS Stock, possibly for the Mini14/30 and 10/22 stocks as well
postcontent:
For all you guys with SKSs set in Tapco stocks.

I have made up a few of these folding adapters to sell and currently have one available. The pics with the Tapco stock are just for reference on how it looks and how it works. What you get is the item in the first pic. You will need to buy an AR buffer tube to fit your Tapco Butt stock as this will replace the plastic 'tube' assembly that comes from Tapco. Also, make sure you know which tube you need because older Tapco SKS stocks used commercial sizing in the butt stock whereas the newer ones(around 3 years or newer) use mil-spec sizing. If you are not sure do a search on AR mil-spec vs. commercial buffer tube difference and you will find a diagram with the dimensions on it.

EDIT: I have not obtained the stocks to verify, but Tapco has told me the Intrafuse stocks for the Rugers(Mini-14/30 and 10/22) have the same sized cavity for the butt stock tube set up. So, if any of you guys with those rifles and Tapco stocks are interested we could check it to verify fit before you buy.

Price is $35 with you coming to me. Add $5 and I can install it for you. Just bring your stock with the buffer tube over and I'll set it up in about 5-10 minutes. I can also ship it for $5 if you are a little too far away to drive over to my house.
